<br>
Evade styles work if your react-style-attack comes between an attack you evaded and the same attacker's next round.  Thus, if you're using a fast weapon, have good reflexes, or your first reaction attack has a stun, you can get more than one &quot;opening&quot; in before finishing a chain.<br>
<br>
Like Ciardha, I use Diamondback (open: you evade, short stun) with the CS evade chain Hamstring (open: you evade) &gt; Leaper, for a makeshift 3-style chain.  Because of the stun on DB...<br>
<br>
Diamondback &gt; Hamstring &gt; Leaper always works, no skill involved other than hitting the buttons before my own next round, as if it were a &quot;real&quot; 3-style chain.<br>
<br>
Diamondback &gt; Diamondback &gt; Hamstring &gt; Leaper sometimes works, depending on timing.  Diminishing returns on DB's already-short stun means it fails sometimes, so I don't usually try.<br>
<br>
Diamondback &gt; Hamstring &gt; Diamondback &gt; Hamstring &gt; Leaper would theoretically work once in a while but I haven't tried it.<br>
<br>
You too can mix and match style chains! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19>Main Hall</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
